  <description type="morphology">Plants sometimes winter annuals. Stems mostly simple, (1–)3–7 dm. Basal leaves: blade (slightly fleshy), pale green, oblanceolate to obovate, 5–9 cm, margins ± entire. Cauline leaves: blade oblong to elliptic or lanceolate, (1–)3–10(–15) cm × (5–)20–25(–50) mm, base deeply cordate-amplexicaul, apex rounded. Fruiting pedicels ascending, straight or curved-ascending, (8–)10–15(–20) mm. Flowers: sepals 6–8 × 1–1.5 mm, median pair narrower than lateral, apex acute; petals 7–12 × 2–3 mm, base attenuate, claw usually as long as sepal; filaments 5–7 mm; anthers 1.5–2 mm. Fruits ± torulose, strongly 4-angled to ± cylindrical, 1-nerved, keeled, (5–)8–14 cm × 2–2.5 mm; style cylindrical, 0.5–4 mm. Seeds brown, 2–2.9 × 1.2–1.5 mm.2n = 14.</description>
